    id: 17,
    slug: "prepositions-of-time-and-place-at-in-on",
    title: "Prepositions of Time and Place: At, In, On Explained",
    titleAr: "حروف الجر للوقت والمكان: At وIn وOn بالتفصيل",
    category: "Grammar",
    categoryAr: "القواعد",
    iconKey: "target", color: "#38bdf8",
    image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1543109740-4bdb38fda756?w=900&q=75&auto=format&fit=crop",
    preview: "At, in, and on are three of the most misused words in English. This guide gives you clear, memorable rules for time and place.",
    previewAr: "At وIn وOn من أكتر الكلمات اللي بتُستخدم غلط في الإنجليزية. الدليل ده هيديك قواعد واضحة وسهلة الحفظ للوقت والمكان.",
    date: "2026-02-04",
    readTime: "6 min read",
    content: "Prepositions are notoriously difficult because they often don't translate directly between languages. \"At,\" \"in,\" and \"on\" are three of the most common — and most confused — prepositions in English. Here's a clear, practical system for using them correctly.\n\n## Prepositions of Time\n\n**AT — for precise/exact times**\n\nUse \"at\" for exact clock times, and a few fixed expressions.\n\n- at 6 o'clock, at 9:30, at noon, at midnight\n- at night, at the weekend (British English), at Christmas, at the moment\n\n**IN — for longer periods**\n\nUse \"in\" for months, years, seasons, centuries, and general parts of the day.\n\n- in January, in 2026, in summer, in the 21st century\n- in the morning, in the afternoon, in the evening (but \"at night\")\n\n**ON — for specific days and dates**\n\nUse \"on\" for days of the week and specific calendar dates.\n\n- on Monday, on my birthday, on 5th May, on Christmas Day\n- on the weekend (American English)\n\n## Quick Time Comparison\n\n| AT | IN | ON |\n|---|---|---|\n| at 7 p.m. | in July | on Friday |\n| at night | in 2025 | on 10th June |\n| at the moment | in the morning | on my birthday |\n| at Eid | in winter | on weekdays |\n\n## Prepositions of Place\n\n**AT — for a specific point**\n\nUse \"at\" for an exact point or address — think of it as a small dot on a map.\n\n- at the door, at the bus stop, at the corner\n- at 25 Nile Street, at the airport, at home, at work, at school\n\n**IN — for an enclosed space**\n\nUse \"in\" for something inside a larger area — cities, countries, rooms, containers.\n\n- in Cairo, in Egypt, in the kitchen, in the box, in the car\n\n**ON — for a surface**\n\nUse \"on\" for something touching a surface — think of it as sitting on top of something.\n\n- on the table, on the wall, on the floor, on the ceiling\n- on the bus / on the train / on the plane (public transport you can walk around in)\n- but: in the car / in a taxi (small, enclosed private vehicles)\n\n## Quick Place Comparison\n\n| AT | IN | ON |\n|---|---|---|\n| at the station | in the room | on the desk |\n| at the entrance | in London | on the wall |\n| at reception | in the fridge | on the bus |\n| at the traffic lights | in my bag | on the street |\n\n## Special Cases That Confuse Learners\n\n- in bed (enclosed by blankets) but on the bed (sitting on top of it)\n- in a car / a taxi, but on a bus / a train / a plane / a bike\n- at university (as an institution) but in the university building (a physical structure)\n\n## Common Mistakes Arabic Speakers Make\n\n- Wrong: I will meet you in 5 o'clock.\n- Correct: I will meet you at 5 o'clock.\n\n- Wrong: She was born on 1998.\n- Correct: She was born in 1998.\n\n- Wrong: He works at Cairo.\n- Correct: He works in Cairo. (a city is an enclosed area, not a point)\n\n- Wrong: The keys are in the table.\n- Correct: The keys are on the table. (a table is a surface)\n\n## Practice Sentences\n\n- I usually wake up ___ 7 a.m.\n- Her birthday is ___ March.\n- We are meeting ___ Saturday.\n- The cat is sleeping ___ the sofa.\n- They live ___ a small village ___ the north of the country.\n\nAnswers: at, in, on, on, in / in.\n\n## Final Tip\n\nPicture the three prepositions on a scale of size: AT = a point, ON = a surface, IN = an enclosed space. This mental image works for both time and place in the vast majority of cases.",
    contentAr: "حروف الجر معروفة بصعوبتها لأنها غالباً مابتترجمش حرفياً بين اللغات. \"At\" و\"in\" و\"on\" من أكتر حروف الجر شيوعاً — وأكتر حاجة بيتلخبط فيها المتعلمين. إليك نظام واضح وعملي لاستخدامهم صح.\n\n## حروف الجر للوقت\n\n**AT — للأوقات الدقيقة/المحددة**\n\nاستخدم \"at\" للساعة بالظبط، وشوية تعبيرات ثابتة.\n\n- at 6 o'clock, at 9:30, at noon, at midnight\n- at night, at the weekend (إنجليزي بريطاني), at Christmas, at the moment\n\n**IN — للفترات الأطول**\n\nاستخدم \"in\" للشهور والسنين والفصول والقرون وأجزاء اليوم بشكل عام.\n\n- in January, in 2026, in summer, in the 21st century\n- in the morning, in the afternoon, in the evening (لكن \"at night\")\n\n**ON — للأيام والتواريخ المحددة**\n\nاستخدم \"on\" لأيام الأسبوع والتواريخ المحددة.\n\n- on Monday, on my birthday, on 5th May, on Christmas Day\n- on the weekend (إنجليزي أمريكي)\n\n## مقارنة سريعة للوقت\n\n| AT | IN | ON |\n|---|---|---|\n| at 7 p.m. | in July | on Friday |\n| at night | in 2025 | on 10th June |\n| at the moment | in the morning | on my birthday |\n| at Eid | in winter | on weekdays |\n\n## حروف الجر للمكان\n\n**AT — لنقطة محددة**\n\nاستخدم \"at\" لنقطة أو عنوان محدد — تخيلها كنقطة صغيرة على الخريطة.\n\n- at the door, at the bus stop, at the corner\n- at 25 Nile Street, at the airport, at home, at work, at school\n\n**IN — لمساحة محاطة**\n\nاستخدم \"in\" لحاجة جوه منطقة أكبر — مدن، دول، أوض، حاويات.\n\n- in Cairo, in Egypt, in the kitchen, in the box, in the car\n\n**ON — لسطح**\n\nاستخدم \"on\" لحاجة ملامسة سطح — تخيلها قاعدة فوق حاجة.\n\n- on the table, on the wall, on the floor, on the ceiling\n- on the bus / on the train / on the plane (مواصلات عامة تقدر تتحرك جواها)\n- لكن: in the car / in a taxi (عربيات صغيرة خاصة ومغلقة)\n\n## مقارنة سريعة للمكان\n\n| AT | IN | ON |\n|---|---|---|\n| at the station | in the room | on the desk |\n| at the entrance | in London | on the wall |\n| at reception | in the fridge | on the bus |\n| at the traffic lights | in my bag | on the street |\n\n## حالات خاصة بتلخبط المتعلمين\n\n- in bed (محاط بالبطاطين) لكن on the bed (قاعد فوقيها)\n- in a car / a taxi, لكن on a bus / a train / a plane / a bike\n- at university (كمؤسسة) لكن in the university building (مبنى فعلي)\n\n## أخطاء شائعة عند الناطقين بالعربية\n\n- غلط: I will meet you in 5 o'clock.\n- صح: I will meet you at 5 o'clock.\n\n- غلط: She was born on 1998.\n- صح: She was born in 1998.\n\n- غلط: He works at Cairo.\n- صح: He works in Cairo. (المدينة منطقة محاطة، مش نقطة)\n\n- غلط: The keys are in the table.\n- صح: The keys are on the table. (الترابيزة سطح)\n\n## جمل للتدريب\n\n- I usually wake up ___ 7 a.m.\n- Her birthday is ___ March.\n- We are meeting ___ Saturday.\n- The cat is sleeping ___ the sofa.\n- They live ___ a small village ___ the north of the country.\n\nالإجابات: at, in, on, on, in / in.\n\n## نصيحة أخيرة\n\nتخيل حروف الجر التلاتة على مقياس حجم: AT = نقطة، ON = سطح، IN = مساحة محاطة. الصورة الذهنية دي بتشتغل للوقت والمكان في أغلب الحالات."
